Adam Gopnik although, you know,

00:00:12.780 --> 00:00:17.500
I have to confess that only we food
focused people refer to him only

00:00:17.500 --> 00:00:22.250
as a food writer because he has
written about so many subjects.

00:00:22.250 --> 00:00:24.500
It just so happens that I
guess I'm not nearly as much

00:00:24.500 --> 00:00:28.320 position:56%
of a Renaissance man as he or maybe
I just have a shorter attention span

00:00:28.320 --> 00:00:32.510 position:56%
because I find myself quite happily
occupied solely by his food writing.

00:00:32.510 --> 00:00:35.280
And since we are here in the
food room that's what I'm going

00:00:35.280 --> 00:00:37.070
to focus on here.

00:00:37.070 --> 00:00:39.790
Adam has been writing for
the New Yorker since 1986

00:00:39.790 --> 00:00:43.810
and he's perhaps best known for
his work concentrating on France

00:00:43.810 --> 00:00:45.590
