00:10:48.810 --> 00:10:52.790
I actually got up from the
table and like a husband

00:10:52.790 --> 00:10:58.600
in an old 1960s era television
show I made for the door.

00:10:58.600 --> 00:11:01.180
Grabbed my coat and
made for the door.

00:11:01.180 --> 00:11:05.010
And my wife, Martha,
intercepted me at the door

00:11:05.010 --> 00:11:07.100
and we all know those moments
even though you know you're going

00:11:07.100 --> 00:11:10.370
to be coming back we all know
that there are certain trusts,

00:11:10.370 --> 00:11:12.830
certain bonds that
when you break you know

00:11:12.830 --> 00:11:17.820
that they never ever are going
to be remended completely,

00:11:17.820 --> 00:11:20.110
never going to be completely
rewoven, and we were at one

00:11:20.110 --> 00:11:23.260
of those moments and Martha
intercepted me at the door

00:11:23.260 --> 00:11:26.420
and she said you are coming
back and you are going

00:11:26.420 --> 00:11:28.010
to finish cooking that fish.

00:11:28.010 --> 00:11:29.310
[Laughter]

00:11:29.310 --> 00:11:34.580
And I did.

00:11:34.580 --> 00:11:37.580
I knew that I had to.

00:11:37.580 --> 00:11:40.370
I knew that the ultimate
moral taste that was at stake

00:11:40.370 --> 00:11:43.910
with that mouth taste was the
continuation of our family.

00:11:43.910 --> 00:11:49.460
And I went back and I put the tuna
