to go to dinner with Trillin

00:47:36.970 --> 00:47:39.720
because he would take
all the food, you know.

00:47:39.720 --> 00:47:44.090
He's more of a fresser [phonetic]
than a philosopher, Trillin,

00:47:44.090 --> 00:47:48.370
but it's nice that you ask that as
we finish up because I have been

00:47:48.370 --> 00:47:50.730
to dinner with Trillin
from time to time.

00:47:50.730 --> 00:47:53.480
We always seem to end up at
occasions like this and people say,

00:47:53.480 --> 00:47:57.670
oh, they both are big eaters and
Jewish so we'll put them together

00:47:57.670 --> 00:48:03.360
at a thing, but Trillin's
food writing, Alice Let's Eat,

00:48:03.360 --> 00:48:07.980
American Fry, those wonderful
books, totally opened

00:48:07.980 --> 00:48:09.530
up for me the possibility
that writing

00:48:09.530 --> 00:48:12.920
about food can not only be funny
as I hope mine is sometimes,

00:48:12.920 --> 00:48:16.550
but could also be a window
onto domestic delights.

00:48:16.550 --> 00:48:22.350
There could be a way of finding
the whole little play of what we do

00:48:22.350 --> 00:48:26.100
and as a consequence the first
thing you will read in this book,

00:48:26.100 --> 00:48:28.920
The Table Comes First, is the
dedication page for Martha,

00:48:28.920 --> 00:48:33.320
Luke and Olivia, my family, who
sit in chair at the nightly table

00:48:33.320 --> 00:48:34.870
and for Calvin Trillin,
who set the standard.

00:48:34.870 --> 00:48:36.170
